snippet: Tens of thousands of Hong Kong residents took to the streets on Monday, demanding the resignation of their Beijing-backed leader.
abstract: Tens of thousands of Hong Kong residents take to the streets, demanding resignation of their Beijing-backed leader Leung Chun-ying, and pressing for promised democratic changes.
lead_paragraph: Tens of thousands of Hong Kong residents took to the streets on Monday, demanding the resignation of their Beijing-backed leader.

headline.main: Hong Kong: Protesters Press Beijing for Changes
headline.print_headline: Hong Kong: Protesters Press Beijing for Changes
